race.comment: BELLA CORAZON (13) took good late ground off Weeping Woman on resumption when third over 1200m at Kembla Grange. Goes even better second-up and she gets a much better set-up for this. Go close. WINGS OF DESIRE (7) well bred mare who returned from a lengthy spell with a tenacious on-pace win over 1200m at Caulfield Heath. Kept ticking over with a 1000m jump out and has the upside to overcome the sticky draw. SUPER NUI (4) cruised across from the awkward gate and had the race parcelled up inside the 200m when a dominant winner over 1400m at Kembla Grange in Midway class. Will stalk the speed and expected to figure prominently. MAID OF MOOLAH (6) went out fast with the rise in weight before folding up in the straight when sixth over 1400m at this track last Saturday. Suited back to the 1300m and can get across from the gate. Each way.
